Chinese company Oukitel plans to release its new K10000 Pro smartphone in June, according to a report by The Verge. The phone is an upgraded version of the K10000, which was launched in 2015. It features a 10,000mAh battery, which takes 3.5 hours to fully charge, 5.5-inch 1080p display, MediaTek octa-core 1.5GHz processor, 3GB of RAM, and 32GB of storage. The device is expected to run on Android. No pricing or additional release information was available.